    "topic": "World Humanist Day - June 21",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "World Humanist Day - June 21",
        "content": "• World Humanist Day is celebrated every year on 21 June and we’ve been celebrating it since the 1980s.\n• World Humanist Day originated in the 1980s through efforts by members of the American Humanist Association (AHA). Initially, there was no single agreed-upon date for its celebration, with different local chapters choosing various dates significant to their communities.\n• Some selected the anniversary of the International Humanist and Ethical Union (now Humanists International), while others picked different meaningful days. The goal was to establish a day when humanists worldwide could unite and celebrate their shared values.\n• By the late 1980s and early 1990s, the AHA and Humanists International democratically agreed to mark a single date as World Humanist Day, aligning it with the June solstice—a time of scientific and cultural importance."
